Description: Baboon amulet made of faience with only the core preserved, the outer layer of glazing has decayed. Front part with relief, showing a standing baboon, faced to the right, head is broken off. Both arms hold up in front of face, hands broken off. Would have had a perforation probably above the head, but it is not preserved.
Findspot: Excavated/Findspot: Amara West (Nubia), D12.1, lowest floor
Bibliographic references: Spencer 1997 / Amara West I, The Architectural Report (p. 166)
